commit.message: Fixing formatting on the Readme markup.
Adding MPTCP over PPP, Air and Ground Configs
Updating documentation to cover new content

Correcting layer_handlers.cc to reference common members of the tcphdr struct/union.  In this case, th_off became doff to be consistent with the use of rst, syn, fin, etc.  This change should alleviate the need to define __FAVOR_BSD and so the option has been removed from the Makefile.
Cleaning up Makefile and adding -D__FAVOR_BSD per issue opened on 2018-03-11

Adding a '-x' option to mptcpplot which will construct a graph with relative time.  The existing '-r' option for relative sequence numbers is being deprecated in favor of '-y'.  Both '-x' and '-y' can be used at the same time.
Adding a sym link for README to play nice with github

Adding network-traffic-analysis-tools, A collection of applications written in C to help both *analyze* and *visualize* MPTCP packet traces.

mptcpsplit - Split out or list individual MPTCP connections from a file.

mptcpcrunch  - Read in trace files containing a single MPTCP connection and output connection information.

mptcpplot - Generate MPTCP connection-level time sequence graphs.
